special_powers.name: ESPIONAGE: FIGHT ON OUR TERMS
special_powers.description: If Captain America is part of a themed team, opponents do not modify the result of the roll to establish the first player.

special_powers.name: I'M PRETTY GOOD WITH THE SHIELD
special_powers.description: When Captain America makes a ranged combat attack and hits, after actions resolve, he may make a second ranged attack with a locked damage value of 2 as a free action. When he does, he draws lines of fire and counts range from the hit character's square.

special_powers.name: MINION: COMBINED FIREPOWER
special_powers.description: Give S.H.I.E.L.D. Soldier a power action when a friendly character with the S.H.I.E.L.D. keyword and a higher point value is within 8 squares and choose one: Empower or Enhancement. S.H.I.E.L.D. Soldier can use the chosen power this turn.

special_powers.name: ESPIONAGE: DOUBLE AGENT
special_powers.description: When Black Widow is part of a themed team and she uses Probability Control as a result, you may reduce the number of times your opponent can use Probability Control from being a themed team, instead of you. When she uses Probability Control as a result of being part of a themed team, she is not given an action token.

special_powers.name: SPYCRAFT
special_powers.description: Black Widow can use Outwit, Running Shot, and Stealth.

special_powers.name: WIDOW'S STING
special_powers.description: Black Widow can use Incapacitate. When she does, after actions resolve, hit characters are also dealt 1 penetrating damage.

special_powers.name: . . . THE LEAPER
special_powers.description: Batroc can use Leap/Climb and Sidestep.

special_powers.name: SAVATE TRAINING
special_powers.description: Batroc can use Charge and Flurry.

special_powers.name: TAKE A BULLET IN THE LINE OF DUTY
special_powers.description: When a friendly character with the S.H.I.E.L.D. keyword and a higher point value is within 8 squares, that character can use Mastermind, but only to deal damage to friendly characters with the name S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent.

special_powers.name: AERIAL COMBAT SPECIALIST
special_powers.description: Falcon's attack value is not modified by the Move and Attack ability.

special_powers.name: TACTICAL FLIGHT HARNESS
special_powers.description: Falcon can use Energy Shield/Deflection and Toughness.

special_powers.name: GOT YOUR 6!
special_powers.description: Give Falcon a free action and choose one: Empower, Enhancement, or Sidestep. Falcon and friendly characters named Captain America adjacent when this action begins can use the chosen power until your next turn.

special_powers.name: FIELD TRAINING
special_powers.description: When adjacent to a friendly character with the S.H.I.E.L.D. keyword, S.H.I.E.L.D. Commander can use Empower and Enhancement.

special_powers.name: SNIPER'S NEST
special_powers.description: Once per game, give Winter Soldier a power action, place three Sniper's Nest terrain markers on the map, and place Winter Soldier in one of these squares. When he occupies one of these markers, he can use Ranged Combat Expert, lines of fire can't be drawn to him, and he may not be given actions except power actions to use Ranged Combat Expert. Once per turn, you may place Winter Soldier in the square of a different one of his Sniper's Nest markers. When an opposing character becomes adjacent to one of these markers, roll a d6 that can't be rerolled. On a result of 1 or 2, place Winter Soldier in the square of a different one of his Sniper's Nest markers. On a 3-6, remove the marker and, if Winter Soldier occupies that square, place him in another of his Sniper's Nest markers if there is one on the map.

special_powers.name: I HAVE MY ORDERS
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, roll a d6. On a result of 5 or 6, remove an action token from Winter Soldier.

special_powers.name: NO MORE TIME FOR DISGUISES
special_powers.description: Give Steve Rogers a power action that deals no pushing damage and replace this character with CA:TWS #001 Captain America on its orange starting line. When you do, the replaced character may make a close or ranged combat attack as a free action. This power can't be countered.

special_powers.name: NOT JUST A SOLDIER
special_powers.description: Steve Rogers can use Outwit and Shape Change.

special_powers.name: PLAYING BOTH SIDES
special_powers.description: Once per turn, Maria Hill can use Outwit. When she does, she can be given a power action instead of a free action to count range and draw lines of fire from an opposing character.

special_powers.name: THE SHIELD IS MORE THAN JUST A SYMBOL
special_powers.description: At the beginning of your turn, if Captain America has no action tokens, place a Shield Token on this card if it doesn't have one already. When Captain America has a Shield Token on this card, he can use Energy Shield/Deflection, Running Shot and has a range value of 6.  After Captain America makes a ranged combat attack, remove the Shield Token unless the attack was a hit and the attack roll was doubles.

special_powers.name: THE STAR-SPANGLED MAN WITH THE PLAN
special_powers.description: Captain America can use Leadership and Perplex. When he uses Leadership, adjacent friendly characters are considered to have a lower point value if they share a keyword with Captain America.

special_powers.name: ESPIONAGE: SENT TO SPY
special_powers.description: If Agent 13 is part of a themed team, during your first turn, choose a keyword. Each opposing character with that keyword can't be given more than one free action per turn.

special_powers.name: LET YOUR GUARD DOWN
special_powers.description: Adjacent opposing characters can't use defense powers.

special_powers.name: ON THE MOVE
special_powers.description: Adjacent friendly characters can use Sidestep.

special_powers.name: WHATEVER MY TEAM NEEDS
special_powers.description: Agent Sitwell can use Perplex. Agent Sitwell can be given a power action instead of a free action to use Perplex, and when he does, he targets all adjacent friendly characters that share a keyword with him to modify the same combat value except damage by +1.

special_powers.name: ESPIONAGE: PUTTING THE PIECES IN PLACE
special_powers.description: If Nick Fury is part of a themed team, at the beginning of the game, you may place your opponent's objects.

special_powers.name: L.M.D.
special_powers.description: Nick Fury can use Combat Reflexes. When turning the dial, if this click is revealed due to damage taken from an opponent's attack, stop turning the dial. This power can't be ignored.

special_powers.name: COMMANDING OFFICER
special_powers.description: Nick Fury can use Leadership. When he uses Leadership, adjacent friendly characters are considered a lower point value if they share a keyword with Nick Fury.

special_powers.name: A CONFLICTED MIND
special_powers.description: Give an adjacent character a power action to modify Winter Solder's attack or damage value by +1 or -1. This modifier lasts until this trait is used again or there are no other friendly characters on the map.

special_powers.name: I'D BETTER HANG ON TO THIS
special_powers.description: Winter Soldier can use Outwit, but only to counter attack and damage powers of adjacent characters. When he does, he doesn't need line of fire and can use the countered power until his next turn.

special_powers.name: ESPIONAGE & TACTICS
special_powers.description: Captain America and Black Widow can use Stealth.

special_powers.name: SHIELD & STING
special_powers.description: When Captain America and Black Widow use the Duo Attack ability, they can use Incapacitate instead of one of the attacks.

special_powers.name: WORKING TOGETHER
special_powers.description: When Captain America and Black Widow use the Duo Attack Ability, they may target more than one character with a ranged combat attack and ignore damage modifiers from the Damage Depletion Modifier.

special_powers.name: I'VE GOT YOUR BACK
special_powers.description: Captain America and Bucky can use Energy Shield/Deflection, Super Senses, and Toughness.

special_powers.name: HIT THEM HARD & SOFTEN THEM UP
special_powers.description: When Captain America and Bucky use the Duo Attack ability, they can use Penetrating/Psychic Blast instead of one of their attacks.

special_powers.name: INSPIRING PRESENCE
special_powers.description: Captain America and Bucky can use Leadership. Friendly characters within 8 squares that share a keyword with Captain America and Bucky can use Willpower.

special_powers.name: STEALTH SUIT
special_powers.description: If Captain America does not make an attack during your turn, Captain America can use Stealth until your next turn. When Captain America has no action tokens, he can use Improved Movement: Hindering.

special_powers.name: ALWAYS GET BACK UP
special_powers.description: When turning the dial, if this click is revealed due to damage taken from an opponent's attack, stop turning the dial. This power can't be ignored.

special_powers.name: MILITARY TRAINING
special_powers.description: Captain America can use Combat Reflexes and Toughness.

special_powers.name: SUPER SPY
special_powers.description: Black Widow can use Stealth.

special_powers.name: SOVIET CHAIR FIGHTING
special_powers.description: When Black Widow makes a close combat attack, she can use Willpower this turn.

special_powers.name: RED IN MY LEDGER
special_powers.description: Black Widow can use Ranged Combat Expert and Super Senses. When she uses Super Senses, she only succeeds on a result of a 6.

special_powers.name: ON YOUR 6, CAP
special_powers.description: When Falcon is adjacent to a friendly character named Captain America, both characters modify their defense values by +1, if not already modified by this effect.

special_powers.name: AERIAL MANEUVERS
special_powers.description: Falcon can use Sidestep and Charge.

special_powers.name: EYES IN THE SKY
special_powers.description: Falcon can use Energy Shield/Deflection. He can use Super Senses, but only against ranged combat attacks.

special_powers.name: SAVATE, PARKOUR
special_powers.description: Batroc can use Close Combat Expert and Leap/Climb. He can activate Close Combat Expert with a close combat action instead of a power action.

special_powers.name: FOUETTE. CHASSE. REVERS.
special_powers.description: Batroc can use Charge and Sidestep.

special_powers.name: DEVOTED TO THE CAUSE
special_powers.description: Winter Soldier can't be the target of Mind Control.

special_powers.name: KEEP COMING BACK
special_powers.description: When turning the dial, if this click is revealed due to damage taken from an opponent's attack, stop turning the dial. This power can't be ignored.

special_powers.name: MASTER MARKSMAN
special_powers.description: Winter Soldier can use Ranged Combat Expert. When he does, he can use Improved Targeting: Hindering, Characters.

special_powers.name: NOTHING TO SEE HERE
special_powers.description: Give S.H.I.E.L.D. Agent a power action and remove an adjacent debris marker; if a debris marker is removed that indicates a wall or area of terrain that was destroyed, it is no longer destroyed.

special_powers.name: HORDE: FIELD MEDIC
special_powers.description: S.H.I.E.L.D. Support can use Support. When it does, the minimum damage healed is (S).

special_powers.name: HORDE: TRAINED TOGETHER
special_powers.description: When (M), S.H.I.E.L.D. Trooper can use Running Shot.

special_powers.name: HORDE: A PIRATES RESOLVE
special_powers.description: When (M), if Batroc's Brigade occupies water terrain, it can use Sidestep.

special_powers.name: HORDE: EXPENDABLE RESOURCES
special_powers.description: KGB Agent can use Probability Control, but only for friendly characters' attacks. When he does, you may remove 1 KGB Agent from this stack and modify the final attack total by +1.

special_powers.name: HORDE: WELL TRAINED STRIKE TEAM
special_powers.description: When (M), Mercenary can use Sidestep.

special_powers.name: HORDE: EXPOSE YOUR SECRETS
special_powers.description: When (M), opposing characters adjacent to KGB Spy can't use Stealth.

special_powers.name: Open Air Terrain
special_powers.description: If a character that can't use Leap/Climb, Phasing/Teleport, Flight or Great Size occupies Open Air Terrain after actions resolve, deal that character 1 unavoidable damage and then the character's controller places the character in their starting area.
